The order of 7 parameters of the USER's function CONTACT
for a Dirichlet condition on a part of the object boundary
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown
must be

FIXTEMPERATURE( TEMPS, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJECT, NO_OBJECT, TEMPER ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of FIXED TEMPERATURES.

EXAMPLE:
deffunc temperature( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, materiau, temper );
if   materiau=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'dirichlet0' )
then temperature=0; 
else
  if   materiau=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'contact100' )
  then temperature= 100;
  endif;   
endif;
endfunc; 

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
